-- Severn Trent Wins Kansas City Plant Contract on Missouri River
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-01-10T17:57:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-10/severn-trent-wins-kansas-city-plant-contract-on-missouri-river.html
Severn Trent Plc, the second-largest
publicly traded water company in the U.K., said a subsidiary won
a filter system contract for  Kansas City ’s water treatment plant
along the Missouri River.  No terms of the Severn Trent Services equipment contract
for the Kansas City, Missouri, water department’s primary
treatment facility on the river was given in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
